<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1008&amp;p=8626#p8626"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[about Brad Taylor's ref]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1008&amp;p=8626#p8626"><![CDATA[
It is true that one set of attribute bits applies to 4 tiles at once, but the PPU has no such buffers inside it - as such, it will re-fetch the same attribute bytes for <strong>all</strong> of the appropriate tiles.<br /><br />The upside to this is that it makes the MMC5's "extended attribute" mode possible (which uses extra RAM to allow setting <em>per-tile</em> attribute data).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Thu Jan 26, 2006 10:19 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
